> Go for gold in the kitchen with this Olympic Games inspired menu! A popular Greek street food choice, the word souvlaki literally means 'meat on skewers'. However, this vegetarian halloumi version combines indulgence, freshness and flavour all on one tasty flatbread.

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove your @butter{20%g} from the fridge and allow to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @Halloumi{225%g} and cut it into 2cm chunks. Place them into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Halve, peel and slice the @Red Onion{1/2} as thinly as you can. Pop it into a medium bowl and add the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp}(for the pickle). Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). In a small bowl, combine garlic with the softened butter. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

In another small bowl, combine the @Sriracha Sauce{15%g} and @Mayonnaise{3%tbsp}. Set aside.

Cut the @Medium Tomato{1} into 1cm chunks. Pop it in the bowl of pickled onion.

Remove the halloumi from the cold water, pop it onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and dry.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the halloumi and fry, turning frequently, until golden, ~{6-7%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Drizzle the fried halloumi with the @Honey{1%tbsp} and turn to glaze it all over.

Meanwhile, place the @Plain Naans{2} onto a baking tray. Spread the garlic butter over them and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%g} to the bowl of pickled onion and tomato, then toss to combine.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

When everything's ready, share the warm garlic naans between your plates. Pile each naan with the salad and honeyed halloumi. Serve with the chips alongside (or add some to your naan like souvlaki!).

Drizzle the sriracha mayo over the halloumi flatbreads to finish. Enjoy!